[httpimport] Remove the 'module' parameter

As part of Github Issue [1], the 'module' positional argument
in most HttpImport functions are obsolete as they only
limit functionality.

[1] : https://github.com/operatorequals/httpimport/issues/21

[Fix] Handle Exception introduced

A KeyError exception is introduced in later Python version,
and needs to get handled separately.

[Tests] Change Git Cloud References

Test repositories have been created to Github[1], Gitlab[2] and
BitBucket[3] to aid with the testing of this project.

[1] : https://github.com/operatorequals/httpimport-test
[2] : https://gitlab.com/operatorequals/httpimport-test
[3] : https://bitbucket.org/operatorequals/httpimport-test

[Automation] Publish to PyPI on tag

This commit introduces a Github Workflow that will push the `httpimport` module to PyPI on push of a tag.

[Automation][Fix] Add 'pypandoc' to build step

PyPI needs an RST description file to get posted in the project's frontpage.
The `setup.py` uses `pypandoc` to convert the Markdown `README.md` to RST.
The package was missing and is added in this commit.

[Lint] Rehash the whole project with PEP8

Used `autopep8` to make all `*.py` files as compatible with PEP8
as possible.

[Setup] Follow Python docs for Markdown Description

Use the Python docs [1] snippet to use Markdown for PyPI description.

[1] : https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/tutorials/packaging-projects/#configuring-metadata

[Automation] Add Build and Push testing

Make the Python Package Test to also build the project and push it
to PyPI under the testing repo [1]

[1] : https://test.pypi.org/legacy/

[Automation][Fix] Do not fail when an tag exists

When a tag is pushed to PyPI, the workflow fails when the release
exists.
With this parameter, the actual upload is skipped when the tag
is already released.
